Here’s a ready-to-run script for Oracle Linux / RHEL / CentOS VMs in VMware Workstation that will:

1) Install open-vm-tools and desktop components.
2) Enable and start the VMware Tools service.
3) Create a mount point for shared folders (/mnt/hgfs).
4) Mount all shared folders automatically.

Oracle Linux / RHEL Script for VMware Shared Folders:

#!/bin/bash
# Script to install open-vm-tools and mount VMware shared folders

# 1. Update system
sudo yum update -y

# 2. Install open-vm-tools and desktop tools
sudo yum install -y open-vm-tools open-vm-tools-desktop fuse

# 3. Enable and start vmtoolsd service
sudo systemctl enable vmtoolsd
sudo systemctl start vmtoolsd

# 4. Create mount point for shared folders
sudo mkdir -p /mnt/hgfs

# 5. Mount VMware Shared Folders
sudo vmhgfs-fuse .host:/ /mnt/hgfs -o allow_other

# 6. Add to fstab for auto-mount at boot
FSTAB_LINE=".host:/ /mnt/hgfs fuse.vmhgfs-fuse allow_other 0 0"
grep -qxF "$FSTAB_LINE" /etc/fstab || echo "$FSTAB_LINE" | sudo tee -a /etc/fstab

echo "✅ open-vm-tools installed and shared folders mounted at /mnt/hgfs"
echo "You can access your Windows shared folders now."

**************************************************************************
Usage Instructions: 

1) Save the script as setup_vmware_shared.sh on your Linux VM.
2) Make it executable:
   chmod +x setup_vmware_shared.sh

3) Run the script:
   sudo ./setup_vmware_shared.sh

4) Reboot the VM:
sudo reboot

After reboot, your Windows shared folders will be available at:
/mnt/hgfs/

You can now copy files using:
cp /mnt/hgfs/shared_folder_name/file.txt /home/oracle/
